args.Tweet-Instagram-Text-Content: For the past 20 years, my dad has been a pillar of my life. Two days ago, he passed away because of ruptured brain aneurysm. And because of the Coronavirus, I could neither see him for the last time nor attend his funeral. I wanted to post this as a way of expressing my feelings and I also wanted to tell everyone that for those who still have your parents, please treasure them infinitely because life does happen and it sucks. For those who went through or are going through the same thing as me, know that you can always cry with me as a way of releasing your emotions. Stay safe in this world pandemic, everyone!

args.Tweet-Instagram-Text-Content: This post is even sappier than I meant to be now that senior year has been cut short BUT if you knew me at all freshmen year you know that getting a diploma from this university is kind of shocking, i spent all of freshman year & 1/2 of sophomore year crying, I was having the time of my life dont get me wrong but I could never adjust to being 1000 miles from home, I was never really happy, so I left. I said goodbye to my best friends, my sisters, my support group and I went home...dont worry i soon realized Alabama was where I was meant to be & returned, sure it took transferring to Rutgers to make me realize that but it was all apart of the journey and I don‚Äôt regret it. If I hadn‚Äôt left I don‚Äôt think I would have realized how much I love this university, the people Ive met here and how appreciative I am to be able to get a degree from the greatest University in the country. Having my senior year cut short and having to leave the people i‚Äôve spent everyday with is even harder now. But regardless, thank you Alabama for the greatest 3 1/2 (even less now i guess) years and Roll Tide.
